Description: Fragment of round, somewhat irregular, handle to sharp turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine light brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 28a, 1. Name Kallianax. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0146.13.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1184)
